            "title": "The For Loop 🔄",
            "content": "A `for` loop is perfect when you know **how many times** you want to repeat something.\n\nIt has 3 parts:\n1. **Start** (let i = 0)\n2. **Stop** (i < 5)\n3. **Step** (i++)"
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l2_2",
            "type": "code",
            "title": "Counting to 5 🖐️",
            "content": "This loop runs 5 times, printing 0, 1, 2, 3, 4.",
            "codeSnippet": "for (let i = 0; i < 5; i++) {\n  console.log(i);\n}",
